# Kalshi weather-signal pipeline: generate new alerts, check pending ones for
# settlement, run one cycle of the (simulated, real-money-free) paper-trading
# bot, then notify.
#
# Runs ~4-5 hours after each GFS/ICON model init (00Z/06Z/12Z/18Z), giving
# Open-Meteo time to ingest the new run before we poll it; ECMWF often lags
# further behind but the ensemble blend still benefits from whichever models
# have refreshed by the time this fires.
#
# Settlement checking has its own, much tighter schedule below (see
# run_settlement_cycle.sh) — added 2026-07-20 after a real gap: waiting for
# this slower 4x/day cadence meant a market that settled shortly after one
# check could sit unrecognized (paper position still "open", its cash still
# "tied up") for up to ~6 hours before the next one caught it. The settlement
# check itself is cheap (one paginated get_markets() call per series, not one
# per pending market — see mark_settled_alerts.py's own docstring), so there's
# no real cost to running it every 15 minutes independent of the slower
# forecast/price refresh above.
#
# Install (after replacing /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market below with the
# real deployment path — cron needs an absolute path, it won't expand ~ or
# resolve relative paths):
#   crontab scheduler/crontab.example
#
# This repo doesn't manage log rotation — logrotate or similar on the host
# should own that if the log file grows large.

0 5,11,17,23 * * * /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/scheduler/run_pipeline.sh >> /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/logs/pipeline.log 2>&1
*/15 * * * * /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/scheduler/run_settlement_cycle.sh >> /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/logs/settlement_cycle.log 2>&1
# Same-day observation refresh — added 2026-07-20 after scripts/measure_
# pipeline_latency.py found a real, measured Brier cost from the 6-hourly
# cadence above being the only thing that ever refreshed observed_so_far (see
# run_observation_refresh.sh for the full reasoning and numbers). 15 minutes,
# matching the settlement cycle's own precedent — comfortably tighter than
# the hourly METAR cadence this is trying to keep pace with, and cheap for
# the same reason: no Open-Meteo refetch, just one NWS call + one Kalshi
# get_markets() call per city.
*/15 * * * * /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/scheduler/run_observation_refresh.sh >> /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/logs/observation_refresh.log 2>&1
# Weekly re-fit of the bias/std calibration (see run_recalibration.sh for why
# weekly rather than daily). Sunday 09:00 UTC = 01:00/02:00 Pacific, chosen to
# sit well clear of the 05/11/17/23 pipeline slots so the two never contend for
# the single vCPU -- this is by far the heaviest job here on a cold cache.
0 9 * * 0 /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/scheduler/run_recalibration.sh >> /path/to/kalshi-prediction-market/logs/recalibration.log 2>&1
